## About

This repository implements the **Baum-Welch algorithm** (the EM algorithm for Hidden Markov Models) from scratch in Python.

### What it computes
- **π** — Initial state distribution
- **A** — Transition matrix
- **B** — Emission matrix
- **P(O | λ)** — Probability of the observed sequence given the model
- **α, β, γ, ξ** — Forward, backward, gamma, and xi values at each iteration *(optional output)*

### Visualizations
- `log P(O|λ)` vs. iterations (convergence curve)
- `|Δ log P(O|λ)|` — convergence rate
- Transition matrix **A** heatmap
- Emission matrix **B** heatmap
- Initial distribution **π** bar chart
- **γ** (state posteriors) over time
- **α** (forward probabilities) over time
- **β** (backward probabilities) over time
- State transition diagram

