## Algorithm Overview

The Baum-Welch algorithm iteratively re-estimates HMM parameters using the EM framework:

```
Initialize A, B, π randomly

Repeat until convergence:
  E-step:
    Compute α (forward algorithm)
    Compute β (backward algorithm)
    Compute γ = P(q_t = i | O, λ)
    Compute ξ = P(q_t=i, q_{t+1}=j | O, λ)

  M-step:
    Update π ← γ_1
    Update A ← sum(ξ) / sum(γ)
    Update B ← sum(γ where obs=k) / sum(γ)

Until |log P(O|λ_new) - log P(O|λ_old)| < tolerance
```

